data.text:
Daniel Wass challenging England's Jack Grealish during the semi-final

at Wembley Stadium.

European 2020 Football Championships.

Group B.

Saturday 12th June 2021. Attendance 13,790.

England (2) v (1) Denmark. AET. (Damsgaard 30m, Kjær 39 og, Kane 104m). Wembley Stadium,

Denmark:

1. Kasper Schmeichel (GK), 3. Jannik Vestergaard (19. Jonas Wind 105 min), 4. Simon Kjær (C),

5. Joakim Mæhle, 6. Andreas Christensen (2. Joachim Andersen 79 min), 9. Martin Braithwaite,

8. Thomas Delaney (24. Mathias Jensen 88 min), 14. Mikkel Damsgaard (20. Yussuf Poulsen 67 min),

12. Kasper Dolberg (15. Christian Nørgaard 67 min), 17. Jens Stryger (18. Daniel Wass 67 min),

23. Pierre-Emile Højbjerg.

England:

1. Jordan Pickford (GK), 2. Kyle Walker, 3. Luke Shaw, 4. Declan Rice (8. Jordan Henderson 96 min),

5. John Stones, 6. Harry Maguire, 9. Harry Kane (C), 10. Raheem Sterling, 14. Kalvin Phillips,

19. Mason Mount (20. Phil Foden 95 min),

25. Bukayo Saka (7. Jack Grealish 69 min - 12. Kieran Trippier 106 min).

** During the game against Finland Christian Eriksen suffered a cardiac arrest.

He was given cardiopulmonary resuscitation on the pitch and taken to hospital. He was discharged

six days later, having been fitted with an implantable cardioverter-defibrillator device.
